<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-05-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="404" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d404">
                    <head>No. 403.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Morgan</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-05-30"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 30, 1883</date>.
                            (Received June 13.)</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 634.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I telegraphed you to day as follows: “Consul
                        at Mazatlan telegraphs that Captain Caleb is provided with competent counsel
                        in appellate court.”</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>P. H. MORGAN.</signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>